# Group Block Storage


## Volumes [/projects/{id}/storage]
Manage your volumes.

+ Parameters
    + id (string) ... Project UUID

### Retrieve all Volumes [GET]
Returns a list of the current projects's volumes.

+ Response 200

  + Body

            {
              "volumes": [
                { "href": "https://api.packet.net/storage/2c9b3a6c-883d-427a-9f17-e72f849236dc" },
                { "href": "https://api.packet.net/storage/08435e09-83cf-4b25-b4b6-bced867abb22" },
                ...
              ]
            }

### Create a Volume [POST]
Creates a new volume in our datacenter.

+ Request

  + Body

            {
              "description": "Example Storage",
              "plan": "storage_1",
              "size": 200,
              "facility": "ewr1",
              "snapshot_policies": { "snapshot_count": 4, "snapshot_frequency": "15min" }
            }

+ Response 201

  + Headers

            Location: https://api.packet.net/storage/932f7363-fdbf-47e9-a577-08025e2e2443 rel="self"

  + Body

            {
              "href": "https://api.packet.net/storage/932f7363-fdbf-47e9-a577-08025e2e2443"
            }


## Volume [/storage/{id}]
A single volume object.

    + Attributes (object)
        + name (string) - read-only
        + description (string)
        + plan (enum[string])
            + Members
                + storage_1 - Standard Plan
                + storage_2 - Performance Plan
        + facility (enum[string]) - Facility Location
            + Members
                + ewr1 - Parsippany, NJ
        + size (int) - expressed in GB. Min size is 10GB, max size is 15000GB.
        + snapshot_policies (object)
          + snapshot_count (int)
          + snapshot_frequency (enum[string])
            + Members
              + 1min
              + 15min
              + 1hour
              + 1day
              + 1week
              + 1month
              + 1year

+ Parameters
    + id (string) ... The volume ID in the form of an UUID.

